---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { personSchema } from "../lib/schema";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";

const schema = [personSchema()];
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Operator rebuilding in public across sectors." schema={schema}>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>/about</h1>
    <p class="text-fg-secondary text-sm mb-8">Operator rebuilding in public across sectors — AI agents, self-hosted infra, crypto tooling, ventures.</p>
    <p>
      I'm Jordan Newell. I build and operate the systems behind ambitious ventures —
      a self-hosted fleet of AI agents, infrastructure across a dozen hosts, and a
      growing collection of software projects I'm bringing into the world.
    </p>
    <p>
      I'm starting this blog at a moment of forced clarity: a critical-influx week
      where my main infrastructure host went down at the worst possible time, and I
      haven't shipped a product or flipped a business yet. Instead of treating that
      as a liability, I'm making it the premise.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>This is the operator's desk.</strong> Field notes, post-mortems,
      manifestos when warranted.
    </p>
    <p>
      <em>Influences: Byrne Hobart's rigor, Justin Murphy's edge. The first is the default; the second is for claims worth stopping the room.</em>
    </p>

    <h2>What I'm working on</h2>
    <p>
      See <a href="/now">/now</a> for current focus. See <a href="/projects">/projects</a>
      for the portfolio surface. See <a href="/contributions">/contributions</a> for
      OSS work I've shipped to others' projects.
    </p>

    <h2>What I do</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Day job.</strong> Defense and federal IT at <a href="https://richmondpark.co">Richmond Park Group</a> — CMMC, NIST 800-171, modernization for federal clients.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Ventures.</strong> Real stake, not employment. Currently <a href="/ventures">/ventures</a> — DW Trim, joining as Managing Partner.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>The rest.</strong> The agent fleet, self-hosted infra, this blog.
    </p>

    <h2>Find me</h2>
    <ul>
      {SITE.author.sameAs.map((url) => <li><a href={url}>{url}</a></li>)}
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
